https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/count-digits-factorial-set-2/   ----REFERNCE FOR KAMENTSKY METHOD


https://codeforces.com/group/MWSDmqGsZm/contest/223338/problem/P   ----PROBLEM LINK


FORMULA IS LOG10(POWER((N/E),N)*SQUARE ROOT(2*PI*N))---IMP 


WHEN WE OPEN THE BRACKETS * BECOMES +


N*LOG10((N/E))+(LOG(2*PI*N)/2) ----EXPANDED VERSION 


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
#define ll long long int
#define M_E 2.71828 ///THIS IS THE VALUE OF E
#define M_PI 3.14159 // THIS IS THE VALUE OF PI
int main()
{
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(NULL);
    cout.tie(NULL);
    ll n;
    cin>>n;
    //kamentsky method 

    double  x=(n*log10((n/M_E)))+(log10(2*M_PI*n))/2.0;
    x=floor(x)+1;
    cout<<"Number of digits of "<<n<<"! is "<<x;
}
